How Kubernetes VPA actually works?

Vertical Pod Autoscaler (VPA) uses real CPU and memory usage data to recommend better resource requests.

What happens behind the scenes:
âžœ Live traffic hits Pods
âžœ Metrics Server collects CPU and memory usage
âžœ VPA Recommender analyzes usage over time
âžœ It calculates recommended resource requests

Then it depends on the mode ðŸ‘‡
Auto mode:
âžœ VPA updates CPU/memory requests
âžœ Pods are evicted and restarted
âžœ New Pods start with optimized requests

Recommendation-only mode:
âžœVPA does not change anything
âžœ Recommendations are shown in VPA status

VPA provides:
âžœ target
âžœ lower bound
âžœ upper bound
This helps avoid over- and under-provisioning.

Simple mechanism.
Very powerful when used correctly.
